I suggest investing some time and posts in Drawing Improvement General /dig/. Threads are much slower than hmofa so easier to keep up with, usually last 3 to 5 days minimum, sometimes a bit longer. Show examples of your attempts and ask for feedback and pointers resources that will help you with problems you're facing.

Her tail isn't necessarily too high. That can vary depending on your personal design preferences, but the point about a tail being an extension of the spine is critical to grasp early on. Or you'll end up retconning the design in a few years when you finally realize why it bothers you.
